I see your point. It certainly is more complex under the hood if ByteOrder.nativeOrder() is used instead of IS_PLATFORM_LITTLE_ENDIAN in JITHelpers. I don't think reverting back is a deal breaker. What I would like to see is removal of the isPlatformLittleEndian() native method though. This logic is already duplicated for nativeOrder [1]. We can just reuse [1] instead (Unsafe.isBigEndian()).
@simonameng can you make the appropriate changes?
[1] https://github.com/eclipse/openj9/blob/83f3cbdb4c413343da35f449bb97174c618df478/runtime/jcl/common/sun_misc_Unsafe.cpp#L704-L712
